The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 India make World Cup

 Jyoti Randhawa 

New Delhi: Jyoti Randhawas superior ranking has earned India a direct qualification for the World Cup of Golf 2007, scheduled to be held from November 22 to 25 at the Mission Hills Golf Club in Shenzhen, China. 

Randhawa will team up with Gaurav Ghei to represent India at this prestigious team competition, a statement from the PGTI said on Wednesday. 

Randhawa is currently ranked 102, while Ghei is the next highest-ranked Indian professional according to world rankings. 

This is only the second time that India have earned a direct entry into the World Cup finals. 

The first time India qualified directly was in 2005. The team of Randhawa and Arjun Atwal finished a very creditable ninth. 

I was very satisfied with my performance in 2005 as the team finished ninth. This time, I have an opportunity to improve on my previous performance. The fact that Gaurav is playing fabulous golf at the moment augurs well for our team, said an excited Randhawa. 

Randhawa, for whom it would be the second appearance, has come up with some impressive performances on the European Tour this year. 

He is currently placed 28th on the European Tour Order of Merit, with earnings of 723,279 euros. 

Ghei will be turning out for India at this tournament for the third time. His earlier appearances were in 1997 and 2003 with Arjun Singh and Digvijay Singh, respectively. 

 (PTI) 




